S3 Workflow – Corporate Documentation
________________________________________
Workflow Name:
S3 WORKFLOW
Purpose Summary:
Automates the scheduled retrieval of files from AWS S3 and stores them in a designated local directory for downstream ERP reporting and analytics.
________________________________________
Executive Summary
The  S3 Workflow is an automated data integration process designed to retrieve files from a centralized cloud storage repository (AWS S3) and store them locally for enterprise reporting purposes.
This workflow delivers operational value by ensuring timely, consistent, and error-free synchronization of reporting data. It eliminates manual intervention, reduces the risk of data inconsistencies, and supports business intelligence platforms such as Power BI with up-to-date datasets.
________________________________________
System Overview
Architecture Description
The workflow operates within the n8n automation platform and integrates with AWS S3 using secure IAM credentials. It follows a scheduled execution model, periodically fetching files from a specified S3 bucket and writing them to a local file system.
Data Flow Explanation
1.	The workflow is triggered based on a predefined schedule.
2.	It connects to AWS S3 and retrieves a list of all available files in the target bucket.
3.	Files are processed sequentially using a batching mechanism.
4.	Each file is downloaded individually.
5.	Downloaded files are written to a structured local directory.
6.	The process loops until all files are processed.
________________________________________

Workflow Components
1. Schedule Trigger
•	Type: n8n-nodes-base.scheduleTrigger
•	Function: Initiates the workflow execution based on time-based rules.
•	Business Purpose: Ensures automated and periodic data synchronization without manual intervention.
Configuration Details:
•	Executes every 2 hours
•	Additional triggers at:
o	21:30 (9:30 PM)
o	23:40 (11:40 PM)
•	Timezone: Asia/Kolkata
________________________________________
2. Get many files
•	Type: n8n-nodes-base.awsS3
•	Function: Retrieves metadata for all files stored in the specified S3 bucket.
•	Business Purpose: Provides a complete inventory of available files for processing and reporting.
Configuration Details:
•	Operation: Get All Objects
•	Bucket Name: XXXXXXX
•	Return Mode: All files
________________________________________
3. Loop Over Items
•	Type: n8n-nodes-base.splitInBatches
•	Function: Iterates through the list of files one at a time.
•	Business Purpose: Enables controlled, sequential processing of files to ensure reliability and scalability.

Key Behavior:
•	Processes files in batches (default: single item per iteration)
•	Maintains workflow stability for large datasets
________________________________________
4. Download a file
•	Type: n8n-nodes-base.awsS3
•	Function: Downloads individual files from the S3 bucket.
•	Business Purpose: Transfers required data files from cloud storage to the local system for reporting and analysis.
Configuration Details:
•	Operation: Download File
•	Bucket Name: XXXXXX
•	File Key: Dynamically mapped ({{ $json.Key }})
________________________________________
5. Read/Write Files from Disk
•	Type: n8n-nodes-base.readWriteFile
•	Function: Writes the downloaded file to a specified local directory.
•	Business Purpose: Stores files in a structured local repository for use by ERP systems and reporting tools.
Configuration Details:
•	Operation: Write File
•	File Path:
E:\Daily files\r clone files\
•	File Naming: Derived dynamically from original file name
•	Append Mode: Disabled (ensures overwrite or fresh write)
________________________________________


Process Flow
Workflow Sequence
Schedule Trigger
→ Get many files (S3 Bucket Listing)
→ Loop Over Items (Batch Processing)
→ Download a file (From S3)
→ Read/Write Files from Disk (Local Storage)
→ Loop continues until all files are processed
